INSERT INTO node_revisions
              (nid,       vid,       uid, title,              body,             teaser,          log, timestamp,format) VALUES
              (35,35,1,   'Health Statistics', '<p>Data from the 1999 DIGESA report demonstrates that more than 99% of children in La Oroya have elevated blood-lead levels. The below table shows the medical action recommended by the Centers for Disease Control (CDC) according to the degree of lead poisoning. More than 18% of the 346 randomly selected children studied in La Oroya should have been hospitalized for immediate medical treatment. To our knowledge, none of the children have been appropriately treated to date. While a level of 10 ug/dL of lead in the blood is considered acceptable, recent studies have shown that the effects of lead poisoning, such as weaker academic and cognitive skills, can occur at even lower levels. </p> <p> </p> <p><table class="statistics"><tr><th>Blood Lead Levels (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Percentage with levels within this range </th> </p> <p> <th>Number of children (total of 346 children)</th> </p> <p> <th>Recommended medical attention</th></tr><tr><td>0 &#x2013; 10</td><td class="right">0.9%</td><td class="right"> 3</td><td>None</td></tr><tr><td>10.1 &#x2013; 20</td><td class="right">13.3%</td><td class="right"> 45</td><td>Refer for case management</td></tr><tr><td>20.1 &#x2013; 44</td><td class="right">67.0%</td><td class="right"> 234</td><td>Refer for medical evaluation and follow up. Identify and eliminate sources of lead..</td></tr><tr><td>44.1 &#x2013; 70</td><td class="right">18.3%</td><td class="right"> 62</td><td>Refer for urgent medical attention (within 48 hours)</td></tr><tr><td>> 70</td><td class="right">0.6%</td><td class="right"> 2</td><td>Immediately admit for chelation therapy.</td></tr></table><table class="statistics"><tr><th>District</th> </p> <p> <th>Children tested</td><th>Age</th> </p> <p> <th>Min. (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Max. (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Mean. (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Average (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Standard (ug/dL)</th></tr><tr><td>La Oroya Antigua</td><td class="right">139</td><td class="right">3 - 10</td><td class="right">14.7</td><td class="right">79.9</td><td class="right">42.8</td><td class="right">43.5</td><td class="right">10</td></tr><tr><td>La Oroya Nueva</td><td class="right">162</td><td class="right">4 - 9</td><td class="right">14.6</td><td class="right">67</td><td class="right">26.1</td><td class="right">26.6</td><td class="right">10</td></tr><tr><td>Sta. Rosa de Sacco</td><td class="right">45</td><td class="right">3 - 9</td><td class="right">6.9</td><td class="right">52.5</td><td class="right">28.5</td><td class="right">28.7</td><td class="right">10</td></tr><tr><td>Total</td><td class="right">346</td><td class="right">3 - 10</td><td class="right">6.9</td><td class="right">79.9</td><td class="right">32.8</td><td class="right">33.6</td><td class="right">10</td></tr></table><table class="statistics"><tr><th>Age group</th> </p> <p> <th>Children tested</th> </p> <p> <th>Percentage%</th> </p> <p> <th>Min. (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Max (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Standard (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Average (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Standard Deviation(ug/dL)</th></tr><tr><td>2 a 4</td><td class="right">8</td><td class="right">2.3</td><td class="right">21.7</td><td class="right">67.7</td><td class="right">10</td><td class="right">38.6</td><td class="right">11.2</td></tr><tr><td>4.1 a 6</td><td class="right">84</td><td class="right">24</td><td class="right">6.9</td><td class="right">79.9</td><td class="right">10</td><td class="right">34.1</td><td class="right">14.7</td></tr><tr><td>6.1 a 8</td><td class="right">134</td><td class="right">38.7</td><td class="right">10.6</td><td class="right">68.2</td><td class="right">10</td><td class="right">36.3</td><td class="right">12.1</td></tr><tr><td>8.1 a 10</td><td class="right">120</td><td class="right">34.7</td><td class="right">9.0</td><td class="right">58.7</td><td class="right">10</td><td class="right">30.6</td><td class="right">11.3</td></tr><tr><td>Total</td><td class="right">346</td><td class="right">100.0</td><td class="right">6.9</td><td class="right">79.9</td><td class="right">10</td><td class="right">33.6</td><td class="right">12.3</td></tr></table>A July 2002 indpendent blood-lead sampling study conducted by the NGO "Uniendo Manos Contra la Pobreza" shows that the situation in La Oroya remains critical. Of 78 individuals tested for blood-lead in this more recent study, none had blood-lead levels less than 10ug/dL, and 33 individuals had levels greater than 40 ug/dL. </p> <p> </p> <p> </p> <p>The high levels of other harmful contaminants in the air further exacerbate the health crisis. The levels of <a href="/?q=laoroya.contaminants">sulfur dioxide</a>, toxic metals such as <a href="/?q=laoroya.contaminants">cadmium</a> and <a href="/?q=laoroya.contaminants">arsenic</a>, and particulate matter in La Oroya also greatly exceed safety standards endorsed by the EPA and the World Health Organization. </p> <p> </p> <p> </p> <p> </p> <p> Study of La Oroya blood lead levels by Ministry of Health: <br></p> <p> {DOC DIGESA_blood_Pb_Exec.pdf Executive Summary (in Spanish) [PDF, 184k]} <br></p> <p> {DOC DIGESA_blood_Pb_Main.pdf Main (in Spanish) [PDF, 996k]} <br></p> <p> {DOC DIGESA_blood_Pb_Fotos.pdf Photographs (includes Spanish text)[PDF, 284k]} <br></p> <p> {DOC DIGESA_blood_Pb_Graphs.pdf Graphs (in Spanish) [PDF, 916k]} <br></p> ','', '', NOW(), 1),
              (1035,1035,1,'Estudios de Salud Pública', '<p>A partir de los resultados de monitoreo de plomo en sangre llevado a cabo por la Dirección General de Salud Ambiental – DIGESA – del Ministerio de Salud en noviembre de 1999, se ha podido determinar que existe una situación crítica en la salud de la población infantil de La Oroya por intoxicación por plomo. El cuadro muestra los niveles de plomo en sangre reportados por DIGESA y las acciones médicas recomendadas respectivamente por la CDC en los EEUU. Mas que 18% de los niños analizados debieron ser remitidos urgentemente a un hospital para atención médica. Se considera que el nivel de 10 ug/dL de plomo en la sangre es un nivel aceptable, pero estudios recientes han demostrado que los efectos de intoxicación se producen aún a niveles menores, </p> <p> </p> <p><table class="statistics"><tr><th>Rango de plomo en sangre (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Porcentaje de niños con este rango</th> </p> <p> <th>Número de niños (de un total de 346 niños) </th> </p> <p> <th>Atención médica que se recomienda</th></tr><tr><td>0 &#x2013; 10</td><td class="right">0.9%</td><td class="right"> 3</td><td>Ninguna</td></tr><tr><td>10.1 &#x2013; 20</td><td class="right">13.3%</td><td class="right"> 45</td><td>Referir para manejo de caso</td></tr><tr><td>20.1 &#x2013; 44</td><td class="right">67.0%</td><td class="right"> 234</td><td>Referir para evaluación médica y seguimiento. Identificar y eliminar las fuentes de plomo.</td></tr><tr><td>44.1 &#x2013; 70</td><td class="right">18.3%</td><td class="right"> 62</td><td>Referir para atención médica urgente y seguimiento ambiental (dentro de las siguientes 48 horas)</td></tr><tr><td>> 70</td><td class="right">0.6%</td><td class="right"> 2</td><td>Admitir para terapia de quelación inmediata.</td></tr></table><table class="statistics"><tr><th>Localidad</th> </p> <p> <th>No niños</td><th>Edad (Años)</th> </p> <p> <th>Mínimo (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Máximo (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>M. Geom. (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Promedio (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Límite Permisible (ug/dL)</th></tr><tr><td>La Oroya Antigua</td><td class="right">139</td><td class="right">3 - 10</td><td class="right">14.7</td><td class="right">79.9</td><td class="right">42.8</td><td class="right">43.5</td><td class="right">10</td></tr><tr><td>La Oroya Nueva</td><td class="right">162</td><td class="right">4 - 9</td><td class="right">14.6</td><td class="right">67</td><td class="right">26.1</td><td class="right">26.6</td><td class="right">10</td></tr><tr><td>Sta. Rosa de Sacco</td><td class="right">45</td><td class="right">3 - 9</td><td class="right">6.9</td><td class="right">52.5</td><td class="right">28.5</td><td class="right">28.7</td><td class="right">10</td></tr><tr><td>Total</td><td class="right">346</td><td class="right">3 - 10</td><td class="right">6.9</td><td class="right">79.9</td><td class="right">32.8</td><td class="right">33.6</td><td class="right">10</td></tr></table><table class="statistics"><tr><th>Grupos de Edad</th> </p> <p> <th>No niños</th> </p> <p> <th>Porcentaje%</th> </p> <p> <th>Mínimo(ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Máximo(ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Límite Permisible (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Promedio (ug/dL)</th> </p> <p> <th>Desviación Estándar(ug/dL)</th></tr><tr><td>2 a 4</td><td class="right">8</td><td class="right">2.3</td><td class="right">21.7</td><td class="right">67.7</td><td class="right">10</td><td class="right">38.6</td><td class="right">11.2</td></tr><tr><td>4.1 a 6</td><td class="right">84</td><td class="right">24</td><td class="right">6.9</td><td class="right">79.9</td><td class="right">10</td><td class="right">34.1</td><td class="right">14.7</td></tr><tr><td>6.1 a 8</td><td class="right">134</td><td class="right">38.7</td><td class="right">10.6</td><td class="right">68.2</td><td class="right">10</td><td class="right">36.3</td><td class="right">12.1</td></tr><tr><td>8.1 a 10</td><td class="right">120</td><td class="right">34.7</td><td class="right">9.0</td><td class="right">58.7</td><td class="right">10</td><td class="right">30.6</td><td class="right">11.3</td></tr><tr><td>Total</td><td class="right">346</td><td class="right">100.0</td><td class="right">6.9</td><td class="right">79.9</td><td class="right">10</td><td class="right">33.6</td><td class="right">12.3</td></tr></table>Datos de 2002, de un estudio independiente llevado a cabo por el ONG "Uniendo Manos Contra la Pobreza" mostró que la situación en La Oroya sigue siendo crítica. De los 78 individuos que proporcionaron muestreos de sangre, ninguno tenía niveles de plomo menor que 10ug/dL, y 33 personas tenían niveles mayores que 40 ug/dL. </p> <p> </p> <p> </p> <p>Los altos niveles de otros contaminantes tóxicos en el aire hace aun peor el crisis de La Oroya. Los niveles de <a href="/?q=laoroya.contaminants">dióxido de azufre</a>, metales tóxicos como el <a href="/?q=laoroya.contaminants">cadmio</a> y <a href="/?q=laoroya.contaminants">arsénico</a>, y materiales particulados en La Oroya también sobrepasan por mucho los estándares de salud promovidos por la EPA de los EEUU y la Organización Mundial de Salud. </p> <p> </p> <p> </p> <p> Monitoreo de plomo en sangre realizado por DIGESA: <br></p> <p> {DOC DIGESA_blood_Pb_Exec.pdf Resumen ejecutivo[PDF, 184k]} <br></p> <p> {DOC DIGESA_blood_Pb_Main.pdf Documento [PDF, 996k]} <br></p> <p> {DOC DIGESA_blood_Pb_Fotos.pdf Fotos [PDF, 284k]} <br></p> <p> {DOC DIGESA_blood_Pb_Graphs.pdf Gráficos [PDF, 916k]} <br></p> ', '', '', NOW(), 1);
